  "text": [
    "There's a way a woman",
    "will not",
    "relinquish",
    "her pocketbook",
    "even pulled",
    "onstage, or called up",
    "to the pulpit\u2014",
    "there's a way only",
    "your Auntie can make it",
    "taste right\u2014",
    "rice & gravy",
    "is a meal",
    "if my late Great Aunt",
    "Toota makes it\u2014",
    "Aunts cook like",
    "there's no tomorrow",
    "& they're right.",
    "Too hot",
    "is how my Aunt Tuddie",
    "peppers everything,",
    "her name given",
    "by my father, four, seeing",
    "her smiling in her crib.",
    "There's a barrel",
    "full of rainwater",
    "beside the house",
    "that my infant father will fall",
    "into, trying to see",
    "himself\u2014the bottom\u2014",
    "& there's his sister",
    "Margie yanking him out",
    "by his hair grown long",
    "as superstition. Never mind",
    "the flyswatter they chase you",
    "round the house",
    "& into the yard with",
    "ready to whup the daylights",
    "out of you\u2014",
    "that's only a threat\u2014",
    "Aunties will fix you",
    "potato salad",
    "& save",
    "you some. Godmothers,",
    "godsends,",
    "Aunts smoke like",
    "it's going out of style\u2014",
    "& it is\u2014",
    "make even gold",
    "teeth look right, shining.",
    "saying",
    ", with a sigh. Make way",
    "out of no way\u2014",
    "keep they key",
    "to the scale that weighed",
    "the cotton, the cane",
    "we raised more",
    "than our share of\u2014",
    "If not them, then who",
    "will win heaven?",
    "holding tight",
    "to their pocketbooks",
    "at the pearly gates",
    "just in case."
  ],
  "title": "Aunties",
